    <div class="name-block">
      <h1 class="name">Uses</h1>
      <p class="role">The gear and software I actually use</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="section-label">Hardware</h2>
    <section class="section-body">
      <p>One main machine and a handful of peripherals I&rsquo;ve stuck with for years.</p>
      <ul class="uses-list">
        <li>MacBook Pro (M1 Max, 64&nbsp;GB) <span class="note">&mdash; the workhorse; M1 Max is still a beast</span></li>
        <li>Apple Studio Display (1st gen) <span class="note">&mdash; a great screen; eyeing the new Studio Display XDR</span></li>
        <li>NuPhy Halo75 <span class="note">&mdash; fine for now; an HHKB Studio is tempting</span></li>
        <li>Logitech G502 Lightspeed + PowerPlay <span class="note">&mdash; the mouse I never have to charge</span></li>
        <li>iPad Pro 12.9&Prime; (5th gen) <span class="note">&mdash; reading, notes, second screen</span></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <h2 class="section-label">Software</h2>
    <section class="section-body">
      <p>A terminal-first setup I keep filing down &mdash; a few of these I maintain myself.</p>
      <ul class="uses-list">
        <li><a href="https://ghostty.org/">Ghostty</a> <span class="note">&mdash; <a href="/writing/ghostty-applescript-tmux/">its AppleScript support finally got me off iTerm2</a></span></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.zsh.org/">zsh</a> <span class="note">&mdash; oh-my-zsh bloated it into molasses, so I ran fish for years; now back on a lean, hand-rolled, fish-like config</span></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/junzh0u/starship">starship</a> <span class="note">&mdash; prompt; I run my own fork</span></li>
        <li><a href="/built/">mvx</a> <span class="note">&mdash; my own <code>mv</code>/<code>cp</code> replacement</span></li>
        <li><a href="/built/">git-smartlog</a> <span class="note">&mdash; Sapling-style smartlog for plain Git: your whole commit stack at a glance</span></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <h2 class="section-label">Gaming</h2>
    <section class="section-body">
      <p>Console, handheld, headset, and a compact PC &mdash; whatever fits the mood.</p>
      <ul class="uses-list">
        <li>Sony PS5 <span class="note">&mdash; the couch console</span></li>
        <li>Nintendo Switch 2 <span class="note">&mdash; handheld for everywhere</span></li>
        <li>Meta Quest 3 <span class="note">&mdash; VR, when a flat screen won&rsquo;t do</span></li>
        <li>Beelink GTi14 Ultra (Core Ultra 9 185H) + EX Dock <span class="note">&mdash; the gaming PC; the EX dock is waiting on a GPU, once prices come back to earth</span></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <h2 class="section-label">Office</h2>
    <section class="section-body">
      <p>You spend all day here, so it&rsquo;s worth getting right.</p>
      <ul class="uses-list">
        <li>Secretlab Magnus Pro XL <span class="note">&mdash; motorized standing desk; honestly, I&rsquo;m in it for the magnets</span></li>
        <li>Herman Miller Aeron <span class="note">&mdash; with an aftermarket Atlas headrest</span></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <h2 class="section-label">Homelab</h2>
    <section class="section-body">
      <p>Prosumer gear that mostly runs itself.</p>
      <ul class="uses-list">
        <li>Ubiquiti UniFi <span class="note">&mdash; the whole network</span></li>
        <li>Synology RS2423 + RX1223rp <span class="note">&mdash; rackmount NAS for anything that has to persist</span></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <h2 class="section-label">Photography</h2>
    <section class="section-body">
      <p>Mostly pointed at a kid who won&rsquo;t hold still these days.</p>
      <ul class="uses-list">
        <li>Fujifilm X-T2 <span class="note">&mdash; my first mirrorless; now kept mainly for the 18&ndash;135mm and 56mm f/1.2</span></li>
        <li>Sony a7R V <span class="note">&mdash; bought for the autofocus the X-T2 lacked; paired with a 24&ndash;70mm f/2.8 and 50mm f/1.2</span></li>
        <li>DJI Pocket 3 <span class="note">&mdash; pocket gimbal; great for catching the action</span></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <h2 class="section-label">Woodworking</h2>
    <section class="section-body">
      <p>Safety and dust collection first.</p>
      <ul class="uses-list">
        <li><span class="note">Cutting &mdash;</span> SawStop PCS, Festool Kapex, Festool TS 55</li>
        <li><span class="note">Milling &mdash;</span> DeWalt DW735X, SuperMax 19-38</li>
        <li><span class="note">Joinery &mdash;</span> Festool Domino DF 500</li>
        <li><span class="note">Shaping &mdash;</span> Festool ETS 125, Festool OF 1400</li>
        <li><span class="note">CNC &mdash;</span> Onefinity Woodworker X-50</li>
        <li><span class="note">Dust &mdash;</span> Harvey Gyro Air G-700, Festool CT 26</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <h2 class="section-label">3D Printing</h2>
    <section class="section-body">
      <p>My first machine was a Prusa MK3S. Fell in love with Bambu Lab later, especially their AMS for multicolor.</p>
      <ul class="uses-list">
        <li>Bambu Lab A1 + AMS <span class="note">&mdash; open-frame workhorse</span></li>
        <li>Bambu Lab P2S + AMS <span class="note">&mdash; the enclosed one</span></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

